content: He's a rebel doctor who is trying to provide the best care for his patients and protect them from money grubbing insurance companies or chiefs of surgery with over-inflated egos who put the value of a dollar ahead of the patients' wellbeing. content: Conrad's background made him the man he is today, and he's no stranger to ruffling the feathers of his coworkers. Conrad realizes that Bell is past his prime but he doesn't have the clout to have Bell ousted from the hospital, so the series builds tension as the two of them clash. And to be fair, it's not just Bell who has issues with Conrad. The young doctor's unorthodox ??? and occasionally cold ??? methods don't sit well with the rest of the hospital staff, but they tolerate it because Conrad happens to be damn good at his job.
